    <layer level="1" name="Layer 1">
      <focus/>
      <content>Core definitions: Serverless Compute (dynamic server provisioning), Azure Functions (event-driven serverless on Azure App Service), Azure App Service (hosting platform with built-in security), MCSB (security benchmark with controls like identity management), Well-Architected Framework (pillars: security, reliability). Key risks: Shared infrastructure, rapid scaling.</content>
    </layer>
    <layer level="2" name="Layer 2">
      <focus/>
      <content>Standards: MCSB (controls: PL-02 governance, IM-1 identity management, DP-3 data protection), Well-Architected Framework (security pillar). Areas: Platform/Infrastructure Security (HTTPS Only, runtime security), Authentication &amp; Authorization (managed identities, Azure AD), Network Security (VNet integration, Private Endpoints), Code Security (secure coding, dependency scanning), Monitoring &amp; Logging (App Insights, diagnostic logs), Secrets Management (Key Vault references).</content>
    </layer>
    <layer level="3" name="Layer 3">
      <focus/>
      <content>Hands-on: 1. Enable HTTPS Only (Function App &gt; Configuration &gt; General Settings &gt; HTTPS Only: Yes). 2. Configure Managed Identities (Identity &gt; System/User assigned &gt; Add). 3. Integrate Key Vault (Function code: DefaultAzureCredential, Key Vault URI). 4. VNet Networking (Networking &gt; Inbound/Outbound &gt; VNet integration). 5. Enable Logging (Monitoring &gt; Diagnostic settings &gt; App Insights). 6. Code Security (use .NET/JavaScript secure practices, GitHub Dependabot).</content>
    </layer>
    <layer level="4" name="Layer 4">
      <focus/>
      <content>Advanced: Azure AD auth (Easy Auth), Defender for Cloud (threat protection, vulnerability scanning), CI/CD (Azure DevOps/GitHub Actions with OIDC, Trivy scanning), Threat Management (continuous monitoring via Defender, just-in-time access). Holistic design: Multi-layered defense with zero-trust (identity first, network segmentation).</content>
    </layer>
  </scaffolding>
